        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3405060255" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4949468917515749071">Great collection of short stories about being black in America in the 70s, still relevant today during this period of Black Lives Matter. The stories demonstrate a variety of levels of economic status and lots of different situations. My favorite was probably &quot;A Loaf Of Bread&quot; but they were all so fun and thought-provoking. Definitely understand how it was selected in 1978 for the Pulitzer, the first awarded to a black male author.<br/><br/>My rating of all the Pulitzer Winners: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://www.goodreads.com/list/show/142318.Pulitzer_Winners'>https://www.goodreads.com/</a></span>
  <span id="freeText4949468917515749071" style="display:none">Great collection of short stories about being black in America in the 70s, still relevant today during this period of Black Lives Matter. The stories demonstrate a variety of levels of economic status and lots of different situations. My favorite was probably "A Loaf Of Bread" but they were all so fun and thought-provoking. Definitely understand how it was selected in 1978 for the Pulitzer, the first awarded to a black male author.<br /><br />My rating of all the Pulitzer Winners: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/list/show/142318.Pulitzer_Winners">https://www.goodreads.com/list/show/1...</a></span>
