        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2402693732" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15959780348741948247">Pulitzer-prize winning short story collection from 1977. Like many short story collections, they vary significantly, from slice-of-life stories about the african-american community (mostly involving southern immigrants to Chicago) to more philosophical and experimental stories. The stories were probably ground-breaking in 1977, less so now in my opinion, although still enjoyable, and the better ones stand the test of time.<br/><br/>One beef I had with this edition: there is no information on publishing hi</span>
  <span id="freeText15959780348741948247" style="display:none">Pulitzer-prize winning short story collection from 1977. Like many short story collections, they vary significantly, from slice-of-life stories about the african-american community (mostly involving southern immigrants to Chicago) to more philosophical and experimental stories. The stories were probably ground-breaking in 1977, less so now in my opinion, although still enjoyable, and the better ones stand the test of time.<br /><br />One beef I had with this edition: there is no information on publishing history. I have to believe that some if not all of the stories were previously published.<br /><br />Finall, why is this volume (and his other short story collection Hue and Cry) not available for Kindle? These are exactly the kind of backlist books that the Kindle is meant to save.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15959780348741948247" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


