<span id="freeTextContainer2518734831792226894">This was written in the 1970s. I had reserved it at the library when I read about the author&apos;s death and his awards. The cover of the library&apos;s copy is blank so I did not know Elbow Room was a collection of short stories. The first ones in the book were brilliant, I thought. Some of the others were a little weird and the weirdest of all was the title story, &quot;Elbow Room.&quot; I would definitely say this was worth reading if you appreciate skilled craftsmanship with story telling. I think I read that </span>
  <span id="freeText2518734831792226894" style="display:none">This was written in the 1970s. I had reserved it at the library when I read about the author's death and his awards. The cover of the library's copy is blank so I did not know Elbow Room was a collection of short stories. The first ones in the book were brilliant, I thought. Some of the others were a little weird and the weirdest of all was the title story, "Elbow Room." I would definitely say this was worth reading if you appreciate skilled craftsmanship with story telling. I think I read that McPherson taught creative writing at a major university. </span>
