<span id="freeTextContainer16897406975374271799">Elbow Room by James Alan McPherson; Pulitzer Prize winner 1978. Beautiful collection of 12 short stories depicting life in black and white America. The writing is superb and this is now my favorite short story book. My favorite story was A loaf of bread, but they are all great in their own right. Have you read it?<br/>.<br/>“I think that love must be the ability to suspend one&apos;s intelligence for the sake of something. At the basis of love therefore must live imagination.”</span>
  <span id="freeText16897406975374271799" style="display:none">Elbow Room by James Alan McPherson; Pulitzer Prize winner 1978. Beautiful collection of 12 short stories depicting life in black and white America. The writing is superb and this is now my favorite short story book. My favorite story was A loaf of bread, but they are all great in their own right. Have you read it?<br />.<br />“I think that love must be the ability to suspend one's intelligence for the sake of something. At the basis of love therefore must live imagination.”</span>
